Sixteenth Daniel C. Baker, Jr, memorial lecture. Surgical management of supraglottic cancer and its lymph node metastases in a conservative perspective.
 Supraglottic laryngectomy combined with functional elective or curative neck dissection is a priceless contribution toward treatment of supraglottic cancer and its lymph node metastases.
 The history and background of this conservative approach is reviewed.
 Results related to staging are presented.
 Irradiation as a combined or alternative therapy is considered.
